LG has unveiled its new Q series of mid-range smartphones with the launch of the LG Q6. The Q6 will feature the FullVision display design on the LG G6 and is available in three configurations: Q6, Q6+, and Q6Î±. Each configuration has a different memory and storage set-up, as detailed below. The smartphone has a 5.5-inch 18:9 display with a resolution of 2,160 x 1,080 and features a wide-angle front camera. The Q6 will launch in Asia next month and roll out to Europe and the Americas shortly afterwards. LG said the device is aimed at the affordable mid-range segment, but no pricing information was detailed. 